==Arabic alphabet==

===Letter===
'''{{ARchar|أ / ـأ}}'''

# The first letter of the [[Arabic]] alphabet is the small [[hamza]] ({{ARchar|[[ء]]}}) that sits on top of {{ARchar|[[أ]]}}, and the tall column is its bearer. The composite letter is called {{ARchar|[[الف]]}} (’álif) and  the hamza represents a [[glottal stop]] (ʔ). (For the pronunciation without hamza, see {{ARchar|[[ا]]}}.) It is followed by {{ARchar|[[ب]]}}.

===Pronunciation===
'''Combined with fathah:'''
{{ARchar|أ}} — '''ʔa'''.

'''Combined with kasra:'''
{{ARchar|إ}} — '''ʔi'''.

'''Combined with damma:'''
{{ARchar|أﹸ}} — '''ʔu'''.

